In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event. To override, set `Application.Current.UserAppTheme`.

```csharp
// Detect current system theme
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified

// Subscribe to real-time theme changes
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");
    // Update your UI here
};

// Force a specific theme (overrides system setting)
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**In XAML**, use `AppThemeBinding` for automatic resource switching:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />

<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#FFFFFF, Dark=#1E1E1E}">
```

**Full example** ŌĆö a page with a theme toggle and live logging:

```csharp
public partial class MainPage : ContentPage
{
    public MainPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += OnThemeChanged;
        ApplyTheme(Application.Current.RequestedTheme);
    }

    void OnThemeChanged(object sender, AppThemeChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"System theme changed: {e.RequestedTheme}");
        // Only react if not overridden by user
        if (Application.Current.UserAppTheme == AppTheme.Unspecified)
            ApplyTheme(e.RequestedTheme);
    }

    void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        // swap merged resource dictionaries, update colors, etc.
    }

    // Let the user force a theme via a picker/switch
    void OnThemeSelected(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = darkSwitch.IsToggled
            ? AppTheme.Dark
            : AppTheme.Light;
    }

    void OnFollowSystem(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `RequestedTheme` ŌĆö read-only, reflects the OS setting.
- `UserAppTheme` ŌĆö read/write, your override. Set to `Unspecified` to follow the system again.
- `RequestedThemeChanged` fires when the **system** theme changes (even if you've overridden it with `UserAppTheme`).
- `AppThemeBinding` in XAML reacts automatically to both system and user-forced theme changes.
